RetroArch (All-in-one emulator)
specialized for retro emulation,
RetroArch uses modular "cores" (emulators) for systems like 
    Nestopia (NES)
    Snes9x (SNES)
    PCSX-ReARMed (PS1). 
    Genesis, PlayStation, and more

app image           :   https://buildbot.libretro.com/nightly/linux/x86_64/RetroArch.7z
app image           :   https://buildbot.libretro.com/nightly/linux/x86_64/RetroArch_Qt.7z 
flatpak             :   flatpak install flathub org.libretro.RetroArch  
apt                 :   sudo apt install retroarch 

https://www.retroarch.com/index.php?page=linux-instructions

Install cores       :   RetroArchâ€™s interface (Online Updater > Core Downloader).
Load a ROM          :   Go to Load Content, browse to your ROM file (e.g., contra.nes)
Configure Inputs    :   Settings > Input > Port 1 Controls to set keyboards or controllers.

Performance Tweaks  :   gamemoderun retroarch
                    :   Use gamemoderun to optimize CPU/GPU scheduling

Steam Deck Integration  :   Add RetroArch as a non-Steam game and - 
                        :   -launch it in Gaming Mode for console-like play.